  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And whosoever shall speak a word against the son of man, it shall be forgiven him,.... These words, though introduced by Luke among the sayings of Christ, recorded in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " yet were said by Christ, on occasion of the Pharisees, ascribing his works to diabolical influence and assistance; see Gill on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 12:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but unto him that blasphemeth against the Holy Ghost; as the Pharisees did, by charging the miracles of Christ with being done by the help of the devil, when they were wrought by the finger of the Spirit: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "it shall not be forgiven. The Ethiopic version adds at the close of this verse, as in Matthew, \"neither in this world, nor in that which is to come\". ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "it shall not be forgiven. The Ethiopic version adds at the close of this verse, as in Matthew, \"neither in this world, nor in that which is to come\". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
