        "text": "πᾶς ὃς ἐρεῖ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.: the true historical setting of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "logion",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " concerning blasphemy is doubtless that in Mt. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 12:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and Mk. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 3:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), where it appears as a solemn warning to the men who broached the theory of Beelzebub-derived power to cast out devils. Here it is a word of encouragement to disciples (apostles) to this effect: blaspheming the Holy Spirit ",
        "children": []
      },
